    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-17T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-17T09:00:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94112/409: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-17T23:00:00+09:00"
                            >December 17, 1940—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 18—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1331. Shanghai’s 1394, December 14, 2 p.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d602fn54">Not
                        printed.</note> In an interview with the Foreign Minister today I brought
                    orally to his attention the further facts in connection with controversy of the
                    American owned motor vessel <hi rend="italic">Estelle L</hi> and stated that no
                    progress had been made toward obtaining the release of this vessel in
                    negotiations with the Japanese authorities in Shanghai. Our request under
                    instructions for the release of the vessel presented in a <hi rend="italic">note
                        verbale</hi> of December 10 was repeated.<note n="55" xml:id="d602fn55">The
                            <hi rend="italic">Estelle L</hi> was released on January 9, 1941.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to the Department via Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
